                    </div>
                    <span>Nothing very special about this book.  It was more of an encyclopedia rather than a history book.  Leon F. Litwack failed to state his opinions which most history books contain. There isn't nothing else to write about since it was just like an encyclopedia but with more words.  There is interesting facts here though.  If readers are interested in the life of slavery before the civil war, this is the right book for you.</span>
                  
              
